I enjoy these debugging trips – but so many layers…
On a slightly connected note, I vaguely wonder how many implementations of a scrollbar are present in the average IT person’s installation of Windows, when you add multiple versions of .net, Office, browsers, Visual Studio, the unloved Teams, and, and… all the way down to the original implementations lurking, unused and unloved, somewhere in user.
How much faster and environmentally efficient everything would be with all the accretions removed.





