The pde.dll debugger extension used in this post ("You can use the !pde.dse extension to dump the stowed exceptions.") is not included in the WinDbg package. At least, not the one you can get from learn.microsoft.com now (WinDbg 1.2308.2002.0).
Some luck with web searching suggests it's most likely "PDE v11.3 - Copyright 2017 Andrew Richards" which I found from the OneDrive link on the Defrag Show homepage on learn.microsoft.com. (I'm avoiding links because those have been blocked by the comment spam filter before.)
Raymond, I'd suggest you add an authoritative link to the right place in the original post.
